PREMIER Soccer League (PSL) prosecutor Nande Becker has confirmed that the disciplinary committee (DC) hearing for Royal AM was postponed. Royal AM failed to honour their promotion/relegation play-offs matches, as they were still in the process of appealing their demotion from position one in the final GladAfrica Championship log to runners up. Also read: TROUBLED ROYAL AM REMAIN DEFIANT The DC was scheduled to take place on Saturday. However, it was postponed to next Saturday (24 July 2020), Becker said via SMS. “Royal AM brought an application for a postponement without filing affidavits in support of such application. An objection was made to the improper way in which the club was trying to proceed, and the panel ordered, for the sake of fairness, that the club file the necessary paperwork by Tuesday. “The hearings will continue next Saturday.”